 ARRIS Group, Motorola Mobility, Inc., Motorola, Inc. and General Instrument Corporation.\r\n\r\nKevin holds a B.S. in electrical engineering from Drexel University in Philadelphia, PA.  He also holds a MSE in Telecommunications and Network Engineering from the University of Pennsylvania and a MBA from the University of Pennsylvanias Wharton School of Business.\r\n'),(2095,158,'_bio','field_625ef73dbc4e2'),(2096,157,'bio','<strong>Jeff Jury, SVP, General Manager, Connected Car, Xperi</strong>\r\n \r\nJeff Jury, SVP, General Manager, Connected Car, is responsible for the day-to-day operational management of Xperis portfolio of automotive and radio broadcast platforms and products, and leads a team of business and technical professionals focused on driving the global implementation of digital radio, audio and in-cabin monitoring technologies with major Tier 1 and OEM customers. This includes leading several strategic initiatives, including building a multi-industry coalition of product development partners, commercializing the technology, and working with the auto industry, broadcasters, and regulators to bring state of the art technologies to market. Jury has an MBA from the Darden School, University of Virginia, and a BS Information Systems from Carnegie Mellon University.'),(2097,157,'_bio','field_625ef73dbc4e2'),(2098,156,'bio','<strong>Walt Horstman, SVP, GM, Monetization, Xperi</strong>\r\n \r\nMr. Horstman leads Xperis Monetization team that works to increase advertising targeting and effectiveness with advanced data and unique inventory across all devices and platforms, mostly recently as Xperi has entered the CTV and streaming space via TiVo. He oversees the business strategic product roadmap and manages overall business group operations.\r\n \r\nPreviously, Mr. Horstman was President of AudienceXpress, which he built as an entirely new business for Visible World. AudienceXpress is a leading programmatic TV platform, which automates planning, buying, optimization and daily reporting of data-driven TV campaigns across the country. Prior to that, he served as Senior Vice President of Media Solutions at Visible World, a TV technology company that provides advertisers with targeting and customization solutions for their TV messages. Visible World and AudienceXpress were acquired by Comcast. Additionally, Mr. Horstman held senior positions at both Cablevision and Accenture.\r\n \r\nMr. Horstman holds a B.S. in Economics and German Literature from Amherst College and a M.S. in Business Administration, Marketing and Technology Management from the Stanford Graduate School of Business. He also spent time studying German Language and Literature at Freie Universitt in Berlin, Germany.\r\n'),(2099,156,'_bio','field_625ef73dbc4e2'),(2100,155,'bio','<strong>Lane Cooper, Editorial Director, BizTechReports</strong>\r\n \r\nLane has over 30 years of experience as a communications executive, consultant, researcher, editor and reporter analyzing the business and technology industry. He is the Editorial Director of BizTechReports, an independent reporting agency that covers the industry analyst community, and is a Contributing Editor to CIO.com, CSO.com, Network World and Computerworld. In this capacity, Lane meets with over 600 senior technology leaders -- including CIOs, CTOs, VPs and Directors -- every year moderating executive events that discuss emerging digital transformation developments.\r\n\r\nNews services and media outlets that have carried Lane\'s byline over the past three decades include:\r\n\r\n* TechWeb * Optimize * Information Week * Telephony * Tele.com * Communications Week * ComWeek International * InternetWeek * Byte Magazine * Enterprise Systems Journal * Larstan Business Reports * Washington Technology * Federal Computer Week\r\n\r\nLane was the voice of The Washington News Bureau Technology Minute for WTOP radio, the top rated news and information station in the Washington DC Metropolitan area. He received a Bachelors Degree in International Relations from the American University in Washington DC.'),(2101,155,'_bio','field_625ef73dbc4e2'),(2102,154,'bio','<strong>Matt Byrne, GM, Consumer Electronics, Xperi</strong>\r\n \r\nOver the last 10+ years of his career Matt has worked at DTS now Xperi in a variety of leadership roles, starting in the then Connected Home Market Vertical, migrating to Sales Operations, and in 2016 returning lead market verticals inside the company and presently is the GM of the Consumer Electronics Vertical at Xperi.  Prior to Xperi Matt was a SVP at On2 Technologies a propriety video codec company up to its acquisition by Google in 2010.'),(2103,154,'_bio','field_625ef73dbc4e2'),(2104,152,'bio','<strong>Jon Kirchner, CEO, Xperi</strong>\r\n \r\nJon E. Kirchner has been a leader in the entertainment and media technology space for over 25 years. Kirchner currently serves as CEO of Xperi Holding Corporation (NASDAQ: XPER), which invents, develops, licenses and delivers technology under the brands DTS, HD Radio, IMAX Enhanced, Invensas, TiVo and by its startup, Perceive, all to make entertainment more entertaining, and smart devices smarter. Formerly, Jon served as the long-time Chairman and CEO of DTS, Inc. where he led DTS from a small startup to a globally recognized leader in audio enhancement and delivery technology for movies, music and video games. Today, Xperi technologies are integrated into billions of consumer devices, media platforms, and semiconductors worldwide driving value for partners, customers and consumers.\r\n\r\nA dynamic and seasoned executive, Kirchner has an extensive background in developing advanced technology and tools that have helped drive creative storytelling and enhanced the impact of film, music and video game entertainment for audiences worldwide. Kirchners executive and global experience, combined with a strong financial background, contributes to a unique skillset that has enabled him to build multiple successful businesses in different markets. He has successfully raised public and private capital, led strategy development and implementation, driven international expansion, managed licensing and business development activities, built premium brands, and created a loyal, professional, passionate and team-oriented employee culture.\r\n\r\nAs the leader of a complex business over a long tenure, Kirchner has guided Xperi through many dynamic phases of innovation, growth and change, from start up to rapid international expansion, from divesting major segments of its business to large scale M&A, and from a solely entertainment-focused company to a much more broad and diverse consumer experience business serving the entertainment, media, semiconductor markets. Through strong vision, partnership, people skills and competitive drive, Kirchner continues to make an impact on Xperi as he further works to build one of the industrys most successful, independent and highly valued technology companies.\r\n'),(2105,152,'_bio','field_625ef73dbc4e2'),(2106,182,'inline_featured_image','0'),(2107,182,'_edit_lock','1651777070:2'),(2108,182,'_edit_last','2'),(2109,183,'_wp_attached_file','2022/04/JohnathanSteuer.jpeg'),(2110,183,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:480;s:6:\"height\";i:480;s:4:\"file\";s:28:\"2022/04/JohnathanSteuer.jpeg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:2:{s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:28:\"JohnathanSteuer-300x300.jpeg\";s:5:\"width\";i:300;s:6:\"height\";i:300;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:28:\"JohnathanSteuer-150x150.jpeg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:12:{s:8:\"aperture\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:1:\"0\";s:3:\"iso\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";s:1:\"1\";s:8:\"keywords\";a:0:{}}}'),(2111,182,'title','<strong>EVP of TV Strategy & Currency</strong><br><strong>VideoAmp</strong>'),(2112,182,'_title','field_6213fedfaf414'),(2113,182,'headshot','223'),(2114,182,'_headshot','field_6213fec4af413'),(2115,182,'logo','231'),(2116,182,'_logo','field_6213fee9af415'),(2117,182,'bio','<strong>Jonathan Steuer, EVP, TV Strategy & Currency, VideoAmp</strong>\r\n \r\nJonathan has been an innovator in emerging media, media research and audience-based media solutions for more than two decades.\r\n\r\nJonathan joined VideoAmp in 2020, where he develops and drives development and industry adoption of transaction-ready cross-platform TV currency data to serve the entire media ecosystem. He is also an expert advisor to the TV Data Initiative.\r\n\r\nFrom 2016-2020, Jonathan was Chief Research Officer at Omnicom Media Group, leading development and deployment of data-driven cross-platform audience-based media tools. Prior to OMG, Jonathan was Chief Research Officer at TiVo, led cross-media research initiatives for AT&T AdWorks, and led media advisory at Iconoculture (now part of Gartner). From 1993-2005, Jonathan co-founded / participated in several pioneering Internet businesses, including Anonymous Media Research (which holds 8 US patents in ACR-based audience measurement technology), Hotwired (the first banner-ad-supported Website), Cyborganic ((too-)early online/offline social media venture), C|NET (first Web + TV content venture) and The WELL (a pioneering online community).\r\n \r\nJonathan holds a Ph.D. in Communication from Stanford (1995) and an A.B. in Philosophy from Harvard. He hails from Milwaukee, Wisconsin and lives in New York City with his wife, two teenagers and three cats.'),(2118,182,'_bio','field_625ef73dbc4e2'),(2119,182,'_yoast_wpseo_estimated-reading-time-minutes',''),(2120,184,'inline_featured_image','0'),(2121,184,'_edit_lock','1651776753:2'),(2122,184,'_edit_last','2'),(2123,185,'_wp_attached_file','2022/04/DavidFinkelstien